HEADWORD: Pilch
<hw>Pilch</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>pylce</ets>,
<ets>pylece</ets>, LL. <ets>pellicia</ets>. See <er>Pelisse</er>, and
<er>Pelt</er> skin.]</ety> <def>A gown or case of skin, or one trimmed
or lined with fur.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

